<section id="installation" style="display:block;">
<h1>Installation</h1>
<p>Install the addon from Blender Preferences: just choose 'Install', select the ZIP or folder, and enable it from the Add-ons tab under the "UV" category.</p>
<p>No special dependencies required. Compatible with the latest Blender versions.</p>
<!-- Replace the src with your Giphy GIF URL (right-click on Giphy GIF > Copy Image Address) -->
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/3o7btPCcdNniyf0ArS/giphy.gif" alt="Installation GIF" />
</section>

<section id="overview" style="display:none;">
<h1>Overview</h1>
<h2>Addon Panel Features</h2>
<p>
The main panel includes:<br/>
<b>Setup Material</b> – Instantly applies the atlas texture to your mesh.<br/>
<b>Unwrap</b> – Unwrap selected faces to the chosen tile.<br/>
<b>Setup Viewport</b> – Enable preview thumbnails for your atlas images.<br/>
<b>Hotkeys</b> – Fast access for common actions, all shown in the panel.
</p>
<!-- Replace with your own Giphy URLs -->
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/26tn33aiTi1jkl6H6/giphy.gif" alt="Panel Overview GIF" />
</section>

<section id="workflow" style="display:none;">
<h1>Workflow</h1>

<h2>Pick Tiles</h2>
<p>Select and assign specific tiles from your atlas palette to your mesh for precise texturing control.</p>
<!-- Example Giphy embed - replace with your GIF URL -->
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/3oKIPnAiaMCws8nOsE/giphy.gif" alt="Pick Tiles GIF" />

<h2>Randomize Tiles</h2>
<p>Automatically assign random tiles from your atlas to create natural variation and avoid repetition in textures.</p>
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/xT0xeJpnrWC4XWblEk/giphy.gif" alt="Randomize Tiles GIF" />

<h2>Scale</h2>
<p>Scale UVs inside a tile for best fit using smooth interactive controls.</p>
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/3oKIPEqDGUULpEU0aQ/giphy.gif" alt="Scale GIF" />

<h2>Move</h2>
<p>Move UVs to fine-tune positions. Live preview allows drag-and-drop adjustments.</p>
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/l0HlvtIPzPdt2usKs/giphy.gif" alt="Move GIF" />

<h2>Rotate</h2>
<p>Rotate UVs to align textures, with 90° snap and free rotation options.</p>
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/3o6Zt6KHxJTbXCnSvu/giphy.gif" alt="Rotate GIF" />

<h2>Highlight & Shadow</h2>
<p>Apply highlight or shadow effects on UVs for subtle lighting and texture variation.</p>
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/3o7btNa0RUYa5E7iiQ/giphy.gif" alt="Highlight GIF" />
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/l0HlBO7eyXzSZkJri/giphy.gif" alt="Shadow GIF" />
</section>

<section id="color-palettes" style="display:none;">
<h1>Color Palettes</h1>
<p>This addon comes bundled with 4 expertly crafted, ready-to-use color palettes designed to enhance your texturing workflow and inspire your creativity.</p>
<p>Each palette features carefully selected colors optimized for game prop texturing, providing instant visual variety and professional results.</p>
<!-- Replace with your color palette GIF -->
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/3oKIPpFhwsMPRWTZUA/giphy.gif" alt="Color Palettes Preview" />
</section>

<section id="gradient-maps" style="display:none;">
<h1>Gradient Maps</h1>
<p>This addon includes a set of 3-4 vibrant gradient maps to enhance your texturing capabilities:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Pastel Sunrise:</b> Soft warm colors perfect for subtle highlights.</li>
<li><b>Cool Twilight:</b> Blues and purples for moody shadows and accents.</li>
<li><b>Forest Glow:</b> Greens and yellows to simulate natural light effects.</li>
<li><b>Sunset Blaze:</b> Intense reds and oranges for dramatic lighting.</li>
</ul>
<!-- Replace with your gradient maps GIF -->
<img src="https://media.giphy.com/media/3oKIPgvPwXi2ZAIS5O/giphy.gif" alt="Gradient Maps Preview" />
</section>

<section id="limitations" style="display:none;">
<h1>Limitations</h1>
<p><b>One object supports a single atlas texture only.</b> Support for multiple atlases on the same object is <span style="color: var(--orange); font-weight: bold;">in development</span> and will be added in future versions.</p>
<p>Some advanced Blender workflows may require custom scripting for full compatibility.</p>
</section>
</main>

<script>
function showCat(id) {
const cats = ["installation","overview","workflow","color-palettes","gradient-maps","limitations"];
cats.forEach(cat => {
document.getElementById(cat).style.display = (cat === id) ? "block" : "none";
});
document.querySelectorAll('nav button').forEach(btn => btn.classList.remove('active'));
const btnMatch = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('nav button')).find(
btn => btn.textContent.toLowerCase().replace(/[^a-z]/g,'') === id.replace(/-/g,'')
);
if(btnMatch) btnMatch.classList.add('active');
}
</script>
